\title{Testing Handbook Generator}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Meta-skill that analyzes the Trail of Bits Testing Handbook (appsec.guide) and generates Claude Code skills for security testing tools and techniques. Use when creating new skills based on handbook content.}

\subtree{
\title{Testing Handbook Skill Generator}
\p{Generate and maintain Claude Code skills from the Trail of Bits Testing Handbook.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\p{\strong{Invoke this skill when:}}

\ul{
\li{Creating new security testing skills from handbook content}
\li{User mentions "testing handbook", "appsec.guide", or asks about generating skills}
\li{Bulk skill generation or refresh is needed}
}

\p{\strong{Do NOT use for:}}

\ul{
\li{General security testing questions (use the generated skills)}
\li{Non-handbook skill creation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Handbook Location}
\p{The skill needs the Testing Handbook repository. See [discovery.md](discovery.md) for full details.}

\p{\strong{Quick reference:} Check \code{\startverb ./testing-handbook\stopverb}, \code{\startverb ../testing-handbook\stopverb}, \code{\startverb ~/testing-handbook\stopverb} → ask user → clone as last resort.}

\p{\strong{Repository:} \code{\startverb https://github.com/trailofbits/testing-handbook\stopverb}}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow Overview}
\pre{\startverb
Phase 0: Setup              Phase 1: Discovery
┌─────────────────┐        ┌─────────────────┐
│ Locate handbook │   →    │ Analyze handbook│
│ - Find or clone │        │ - Scan sections │
│ - Confirm path  │        │ - Classify types│
└─────────────────┘        └─────────────────┘
         ↓                          ↓
Phase 3: Generation        Phase 2: Planning
┌─────────────────┐        ┌─────────────────┐
│ TWO-PASS GEN    │   ←    │ Generate plan   │
│ Pass 1: Content │        │ - New skills    │
│ Pass 2: X-refs  │        │ - Updates       │
│ - Write to gen/ │        │ - Present user  │
└─────────────────┘        └─────────────────┘
         ↓
Phase 4: Testing           Phase 5: Finalize
┌─────────────────┐        ┌─────────────────┐
│ Validate skills │   →    │ Post-generation │
│ - Run validator │        │ - Update README │
│ - Test activation│       │ - Update X-refs │
│ - Fix issues    │        │ - Self-improve  │
└─────────────────┘        └─────────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Scope Restrictions}
\p{\strong{ONLY modify these locations:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb plugins/testing-handbook-skills/skills/[skill-name]/*\stopverb} - Generated skills (as siblings to testing-handbook-generator)}
\li{\code{\startverb plugins/testing-handbook-skills/skills/testing-handbook-generator/*\stopverb} - Self-improvement}
\li{Repository root \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb} - Add generated skills to table}
}

\p{\strong{NEVER modify or analyze:}}

\ul{
\li{Other plugins (\code{\startverb plugins/property-based-testing/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb plugins/static-analysis/\stopverb}, etc.)}
\li{Other skills outside this plugin}
}

\p{Do not scan or pull into context any skills outside of \code{\startverb testing-handbook-skills/\stopverb}. Generate skills based solely on handbook content and resources referenced from it.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference}
\subtree{
\title{Section → Skill Type Mapping}
\pre{\startverb
| Handbook Section | Skill Type | Template |
|------------------|------------|----------|
| `/static-analysis/[tool]/` | Tool Skill | tool-skill.md |
| `/fuzzing/[lang]/[fuzzer]/` | Fuzzer Skill | fuzzer-skill.md |
| `/fuzzing/techniques/` | Technique Skill | technique-skill.md |
| `/crypto/[tool]/` | Domain Skill | domain-skill.md |
| `/web/[tool]/` | Tool Skill | tool-skill.md |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Candidate Signals}
\pre{\startverb
| Signal | Indicates |
|--------|-----------|
| `_index.md` with `bookCollapseSection: true` | Major tool/topic |
| Numbered files (00-, 10-, 20-) | Structured content |
| `techniques/` subsection | Methodology content |
| `99-resources.md` or `91-resources.md` | Has external links |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Exclusion Signals}
\pre{\startverb
| Signal | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `draft: true` in frontmatter | Skip section |
| Empty directory | Skip section |
| Template/placeholder file | Skip section |
| GUI-only tool (e.g., `web/burp/`) | Skip section (Claude cannot operate GUI tools) |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Decision Tree}
\p{\strong{Starting skill generation?}}

\pre{\startverb
├─ Need to analyze handbook and build plan?
│  └─ Read: discovery.md
│     (Handbook analysis methodology, plan format)
│
├─ Spawning skill generation agents?
│  └─ Read: agent-prompt.md
│     (Full prompt template, variable reference, validation checklist)
│
├─ Generating a specific skill type?
│  └─ Read appropriate template:
│     ├─ Tool (Semgrep, CodeQL) → templates/tool-skill.md
│     ├─ Fuzzer (libFuzzer, AFL++) → templates/fuzzer-skill.md
│     ├─ Technique (harness, coverage) → templates/technique-skill.md
│     └─ Domain (crypto, web) → templates/domain-skill.md
│
├─ Validating generated skills?
│  └─ Run: scripts/validate-skills.py
│     Then read: testing.md for activation testing
│
├─ Finalizing after generation?
│  └─ See: Post-Generation Tasks below
│     (Update main README, update Skills Cross-Reference, self-improvement)
│
└─ Quick generation from specific section?
   └─ Use Quick Reference above, apply template directly
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Two-Pass Generation (Phase 3)}
\p{Generation uses a \strong{two-pass approach} to solve forward reference problems (skills referencing other skills that don't exist yet).}

\subtree{
\title{Pass 1: Content Generation (Parallel)}
\p{Generate all skills in parallel \strong{without} the Related Skills section:}

\pre{\startverb
Pass 1 - Generating 5 skills in parallel:
├─ Agent 1: libfuzzer (fuzzer) → skills/libfuzzer/SKILL.md
├─ Agent 2: aflpp (fuzzer) → skills/aflpp/SKILL.md
├─ Agent 3: semgrep (tool) → skills/semgrep/SKILL.md
├─ Agent 4: harness-writing (technique) → skills/harness-writing/SKILL.md
└─ Agent 5: wycheproof (domain) → skills/wycheproof/SKILL.md

Each agent uses: pass=1 (content only, Related Skills left empty)
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Pass 1 agents:}}

\ul{
\li{Generate all sections EXCEPT Related Skills}
\li{Leave a placeholder: \code{\startverb ## Related Skills\startverb \n\stopverb\startverb \n\stopverb<!-- PASS2: populate after all skills exist -->\stopverb}}
\li{Output report includes \code{\startverb references: DEFERRED\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pass 2: Cross-Reference Population (Sequential)}
\p{After all Pass 1 agents complete, run Pass 2 to populate Related Skills:}

\pre{\startverb
Pass 2 - Populating cross-references:
├─ Read all generated skill names from skills/*/SKILL.md
├─ For each skill, determine related skills based on:
│   ├─ related_sections from discovery (handbook structure)
│   ├─ Skill type relationships (fuzzers → techniques)
│   └─ Explicit mentions in content
└─ Update each SKILL.md's Related Skills section
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Pass 2 process:}}

\ol{
\li{Collect all generated skill names: \code{\startverb ls -d skills/*/SKILL.md\stopverb}}
\li{For each skill, identify related skills using the mapping from discovery}
\li{Edit each SKILL.md to replace the placeholder with actual links}
\li{Validate cross-references exist (no broken links)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Agent Prompt Template}
\p{See \strong{[agent-prompt.md](agent-prompt.md)} for the full prompt template with:}

\ul{
\li{Variable substitution reference (including \code{\startverb pass\stopverb} variable)}
\li{Pre-write validation checklist}
\li{Hugo shortcode conversion rules}
\li{Line count splitting rules}
\li{Error handling guidance}
\li{Output report format}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Collecting Results}
\p{After Pass 1: Aggregate output reports, verify all skills generated. After Pass 2: Run validator to check cross-references.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Handling Agent Failures}
\p{If an agent fails or produces invalid output:}

\pre{\startverb
| Failure Type | Detection | Recovery Action |
|--------------|-----------|-----------------|
| Agent crashed | No output report | Re-run single agent with same inputs |
| Validation failed | Output report shows errors | Check gaps/warnings, manually patch or re-run |
| Wrong skill type | Content doesn't match template | Re-run with corrected `type` parameter |
| Missing content | Output report lists gaps | Accept if minor, or provide additional `related_sections` |
| Pass 2 broken ref | Validator shows missing skill | Check if skill was skipped, update reference |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Important:} Do NOT re-run the entire parallel batch for a single agent failure. Fix individual failures independently.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Single-Skill Regeneration}
\p{To regenerate a single skill without re-running the entire batch:}

\pre{\startverb
# Regenerate single skill (Pass 1 - content only)
"Use testing-handbook-generator to regenerate the {skill-name} skill from section {section_path}"

# Example:
"Use testing-handbook-generator to regenerate the libfuzzer skill from section fuzzing/c-cpp/10-libfuzzer"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Regeneration workflow:}}

\ol{
\li{Re-read the handbook section for fresh content}
\li{Apply the appropriate template}
\li{Write to \code{\startverb skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md\stopverb} (overwrites existing)}
\li{Re-run Pass 2 for that skill only to update cross-references}
\li{Run validator on the single skill: \code{\startverb uv run scripts/validate-skills.py --skill {skill-name}\stopverb}}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Output Location}
\p{Generated skills are written to:}

\pre{\startverb
skills/[skill-name]/SKILL.md
\stopverb}

\p{Each skill gets its own directory for potential supporting files (as siblings to testing-handbook-generator).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Checklist}
\p{Before delivering generated skills:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] All handbook sections analyzed (Phase 1)}
\li{[ ] Plan presented to user before generation (Phase 2)}
\li{[ ] Parallel agents launched - one per skill (Phase 3)}
\li{[ ] Templates applied correctly per skill type}
\li{[ ] Validator passes: \code{\startverb uv run scripts/validate-skills.py\stopverb}}
\li{[ ] Activation testing passed - see [testing.md](testing.md)}
\li{[ ] Main \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb} updated with generated skills table}
\li{[ ] \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb} Skills Cross-Reference graph updated}
\li{[ ] Self-improvement notes captured}
\li{[ ] User notified with summary}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Post-Generation Tasks}
\subtree{
\title{1. Update Main README}
\p{After generating skills, update the repository's main \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb} to list them.}

\p{\strong{Format:} Add generated skills to the same "Available Plugins" table, directly after \code{\startverb testing-handbook-skills\stopverb}. Use plain text \code{\startverb testing-handbook-generator\stopverb} as the author (no link).}

\p{\strong{Example:}}

\pre{\startverb
| Plugin | Description | Author |
|--------|-------------|--------|
| ... other plugins ... |
| [testing-handbook-skills](plugins/testing-handbook-skills/) | Meta-skill that generates skills from the Testing Handbook | Paweł Płatek |
| [libfuzzer](plugins/testing-handbook-skills/skills/libfuzzer/) | Coverage-guided fuzzing with libFuzzer for C/C++ | testing-handbook-generator |
| [aflpp](plugins/testing-handbook-skills/skills/aflpp/) | Multi-core fuzzing with AFL++ | testing-handbook-generator |
| [semgrep](plugins/testing-handbook-skills/skills/semgrep/) | Fast static analysis for finding bugs | testing-handbook-generator |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Update Skills Cross-Reference}
\p{After generating skills, update the \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb}'s \strong{Skills Cross-Reference} section with the mermaid graph showing skill relationships.}

\p{\strong{Process:}}

\ol{
\li{Read each generated skill's \code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb} and extract its \code{\startverb ## Related Skills\stopverb} section}
\li{Build the mermaid graph with nodes grouped by skill type (Fuzzers, Techniques, Tools, Domain)}
\li{Add edges based on the Related Skills relationships:}
\li{Solid arrows (\code{\startverb -->\stopverb}) for primary technique dependencies}
\li{Dashed arrows (\code{\startverb -.->\stopverb}) for alternative tool suggestions}
\li{Replace the existing mermaid code block in README.md}
}

\p{\strong{Edge classification:}}

\pre{\startverb
| Relationship | Arrow Style | Example |
|--------------|-------------|---------|
| Fuzzer → Technique | `-->` | `libfuzzer --> harness-writing` |
| Tool → Tool (alternative) | `-.->` | `semgrep -.-> codeql` |
| Fuzzer → Fuzzer (alternative) | `-.->` | `libfuzzer -.-> aflpp` |
| Technique → Technique | `-->` | `harness-writing --> coverage-analysis` |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Validation:} After updating, run \code{\startverb validate-skills.py\stopverb} to verify all referenced skills exist.}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Self-Improvement}
\p{After each generation run, reflect on what could improve future runs.}

\p{\strong{Capture improvements to:}}

\ul{
\li{Templates (missing sections, better structure)}
\li{Discovery logic (missed patterns, false positives)}
\li{Content extraction (shortcodes not handled, formatting issues)}
}

\p{\strong{Update process:}}

\ol{
\li{Note issues encountered during generation}
\li{Identify patterns that caused problems}
\li{Update relevant files:}
\li{\code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb} - Workflow, decision tree, quick reference updates}
\li{\code{\startverb templates/*.md\stopverb} - Template improvements}
\li{\code{\startverb discovery.md\stopverb} - Detection logic updates}
\li{\code{\startverb testing.md\stopverb} - New validation checks}
\li{Document the improvement in commit message}
}

\p{\strong{Example self-improvement:}}

\pre{\startverb
Issue: libFuzzer skill missing sanitizer flags table
Fix: Updated templates/fuzzer-skill.md to include ## Compiler Flags section
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Usage}
\subtree{
\title{Full Discovery and Generation}
\pre{\startverb
User: "Generate skills from the testing handbook"

1. Locate handbook (check common locations, ask user, or clone)
2. Read discovery.md for methodology
3. Scan handbook at {handbook_path}/content/docs/
4. Build candidate list with types
5. Present plan to user
6. On approval, generate each skill using appropriate template
7. Validate generated skills
8. Update main README.md with generated skills table
9. Update README.md Skills Cross-Reference graph from Related Skills sections
10. Self-improve: note any template/discovery issues for future runs
11. Report results
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Single Section Generation}
\pre{\startverb
User: "Create a skill for the libFuzzer section"

1. Read /testing-handbook/content/docs/fuzzing/c-cpp/10-libfuzzer/
2. Identify type: Fuzzer Skill
3. Read templates/fuzzer-skill.md
4. Extract content, apply template
5. Write to skills/libfuzzer/SKILL.md
6. Validate and report
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tips}
\p{\strong{Do:}}

\ul{
\li{Always present plan before generating}
\li{Use appropriate template for skill type}
\li{Preserve code blocks exactly}
\li{Validate after generation}
}

\p{\strong{Don't:}}

\ul{
\li{Generate without user approval}
\li{Skip fetching non-video external resources (use WebFetch)}
\li{Fetch video URLs (YouTube, Vimeo - titles only)}
\li{Include handbook images directly}
\li{Skip validation step}
\li{Exceed 500 lines per SKILL.md}
}

\p{\strong{For first-time use:} Start with [discovery.md](discovery.md) to understand the handbook analysis process.}

\p{\strong{For template reference:} See [templates/](templates/) directory for skill type templates.}

\p{\strong{For validation:} See [testing.md](testing.md) for quality assurance methodology.}
}
}